7
00:00:15,420 --> 00:00:21,490
The Law of Supply and Demand

8
00:00:21,490 --> 00:00:24,850
Any chart is a sequence of supply and demand
zones.

9
00:00:24,850 --> 00:00:29,769
If you’re a beginner, I bet that trading
using classic support and resistance levels.

10
00:00:29,769 --> 00:00:31,750
And there’s nothing wrong with that.

11
00:00:31,750 --> 00:00:36,890
But I advise you to forget about them for
a second, and focus on supply and demand.

12
00:00:36,890 --> 00:00:41,460
If you want to become a smart money trader,
you first need to learn the law of supply

13
00:00:41,460 --> 00:00:42,460
and demand.

14
00:00:42,460 --> 00:00:47,750
According to Wyckoff theory, supply and demand
determines the price direction.

15
00:00:47,750 --> 00:00:51,940
• If demand is greater than supply, the
price will rise.

16
00:00:51,940 --> 00:00:55,720
• If supply is greater than demand, the
price will go down.

17
00:00:55,720 --> 00:01:01,140
• If supply and demand are in balance, there’s
no significant price change.

18
00:01:01,140 --> 00:01:05,820
This is one of the most basic principles of
financial markets.

19
00:01:05,820 --> 00:01:12,479
Now, in any market, there are 2 types of participants:
aggressive and passive.

20
00:01:12,479 --> 00:01:16,729
Aggressive traders are the ones that use “at
market” orders.

21
00:01:16,729 --> 00:01:21,979
They have urgency to enter and attack the
best price possible.

22
00:01:21,979 --> 00:01:26,979
This type of aggressive orders represent the
real engine of the market since they are the

23
00:01:26,979 --> 00:01:30,259
ones that initiate the transactions.

24
00:01:30,259 --> 00:01:33,899
Passive traders are the ones that use limit
orders.

25
00:01:33,899 --> 00:01:39,600
This is important, because the interaction
between aggressive buyers, aggressive sellers,

26
00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:44,000
passive buyers and passive sellers is what
moves the price.

27
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:50,280
The main point is: an aggressive participation
of traders will produce a change in price.

28
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:55,180
Passive orders have the ability to stop a
move, but not the ability to make the price

29
00:01:55,180 --> 00:01:56,180
move.

30
00:01:56,180 --> 00:02:02,600
For the price to move upwards, buyers have
to buy all the supply orders that are available

31
00:02:02,600 --> 00:02:09,229
at that price level and also continue to buy
aggressively to force the price up, to find

32
00:02:09,229 --> 00:02:11,230
new sellers to trade with.

33
00:02:11,230 --> 00:02:17,980
Passive buy orders cause the downward movement
to slow down, but by themselves cannot drive

34
00:02:17,980 --> 00:02:19,180
the price up.

35
00:02:19,180 --> 00:02:25,200
For the price to move downward, sellers have
to acquire all the demand orders that are

36
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:31,060
available at that price level and continue
to push downward, forcing the price to go

37
00:02:31,060 --> 00:02:35,209
in search of buyers at lower levels.

38
00:02:35,209 --> 00:02:40,150
Passive sell orders cause the upward movement
to slow down, but do not have the ability

39
00:02:40,150 --> 00:02:44,670
to drive the price down on their own.

40
00:02:44,670 --> 00:02:49,990
The price needs aggressiveness to move, but
it’s important to take into account also

41
00:02:49,990 --> 00:02:53,310
that the lack of interest from the opposite
side.

42
00:02:53,310 --> 00:03:00,659
An absence of supply can facilitate the price
rise, just as an absence of demand can facilitate

43
00:03:00,659 --> 00:03:02,670
its fall.

44
00:03:02,670 --> 00:03:08,319
In a rising market, as long as the buying
initiative is able to consume all the liquidity

45
00:03:08,319 --> 00:03:14,170
(supply) found at higher levels, the price
will continue to rise.

46
00:03:14,170 --> 00:03:20,150
On the other hand, in bear markets, as long
as the selling initiative is able to consume

47
00:03:20,150 --> 00:03:26,310
all the liquidity (demand) found at lower
levels, the price will continue to fall.

48
00:03:26,310 --> 00:03:32,260
At the moment of a market turn, we will normally
always have a three-step process:

49
00:03:32,260 --> 00:03:33,260
1.

50
00:03:33,260 --> 00:03:34,260
Exhaustion
2.

51
00:03:34,260 --> 00:03:35,260
Absorption
3.

52
00:03:35,260 --> 00:03:38,670
Initiative
During an uptrend, in the exhaustion phase,

53
00:03:38,670 --> 00:03:43,840
there’s a lack of interest of the buyers
to continue buying.

54
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:49,550
During absorption phase, you’ll see more
and more sell orders placed by the smart money.

55
00:03:49,550 --> 00:03:53,420
During absorption phase there are many passive
sellers.

56
00:03:53,420 --> 00:03:56,970
The initiative phase is characterized by aggressive
selling.

57
00:03:56,970 --> 00:04:01,440
More and more aggressive sellers are entering
the market.

58
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:06,430
During a downtrend, in the exhaustion phase,
there’s a lack of interest from the sellers

59
00:04:06,430 --> 00:04:08,280
to continue selling.

60
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:14,370
During absorption phase, you’ll see more
and more buy orders placed by the smart money.

61
00:04:14,370 --> 00:04:18,690
During absorption phase there are many passive
buyers.

62
00:04:18,690 --> 00:04:23,070
The initiative phase is characterized by aggressive
buying.

63
00:04:23,070 --> 00:04:26,750
More and more aggressive buyers are entering
the market.

64
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:32,870
And these interactions between aggressive
and passive buyers and sellers creates supply

65
00:04:32,870 --> 00:04:36,660
and demand zones on a chart.

66
00:04:36,660 --> 00:04:37,660
2.

67
00:04:37,660 --> 00:04:39,310
Supply and demand trading

68
00:04:39,310 --> 00:04:44,320
So, if you are a trader who wants to improve
your trading performance and trade along with

69
00:04:44,320 --> 00:04:50,480
the big players, the first step is to implement
supply and demand concepts into your trading

70
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:51,480
strategy.

71
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:56,030
We already established that the market is
driven by the actions of smart money.

72
00:04:56,030 --> 00:05:01,730
By identifying the areas where smart money
has placed their orders, you can trade along

73
00:05:01,730 --> 00:05:05,090
with them and benefit from their influence.

74
00:05:05,090 --> 00:05:11,789
A supply zone is where smart money has sold
at high prices, creating a bearish pressure

75
00:05:11,789 --> 00:05:14,260
that pushes the price down.

76
00:05:14,260 --> 00:05:20,699
A demand zone is where smart money has bought
at low prices, creating a bullish pressure

77
00:05:20,699 --> 00:05:22,720
that pushes the price up.

78
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:28,729
These zones act as potential turning points
in the market, as smart money often leaves

79
00:05:28,729 --> 00:05:33,490
pending orders at these levels to fill their
remaining positions.

80
00:05:33,490 --> 00:05:40,290
So, in theory, if prices revisit these supply
and demand zones, it is highly probable that

81
00:05:40,290 --> 00:05:43,940
they will be rejected.

82
00:05:43,940 --> 00:05:49,060
To determine the optimal supply and demand
zones, first you need to search for sharp

83
00:05:49,060 --> 00:05:55,060
price increases or decreases, which indicate
the involvement of smart money in the market.

84
00:05:55,060 --> 00:06:00,330
These movements are referred to as market
imbalances, significant price shifts in one

85
00:06:00,330 --> 00:06:01,660
direction.

86
00:06:01,660 --> 00:06:08,300
To identify demand zones, look for fast impulse
moves, keeping a close watch on big green

87
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:09,300
candles.

88
00:06:09,300 --> 00:06:14,540
These candles should have long bodies and
minimal wicks.

89
00:06:14,540 --> 00:06:19,889
Once an impulse move is identified, you need
to locate the base of the zone.

90
00:06:19,889 --> 00:06:26,160
To do so, place a line at the high price of
the most recent red candle preceding the impulse

91
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:33,550
move and another line at the most recent swing
low around the move.

92
00:06:33,550 --> 00:06:41,290
To find supply zones, look for fast declines
and red candles with extended bodies and minimal

93
00:06:41,290 --> 00:06:42,300
wicks.

94
00:06:42,300 --> 00:06:48,610
Then find the most recent up candle before
the sharp down move and place a line at its

95
00:06:48,610 --> 00:06:54,599
low price, along with another line at the
most recent swing high formed at around the

96
00:06:54,599 --> 00:06:56,479
move.

97
00:06:56,479 --> 00:07:02,130
In theory, the price is likely to reverse
once it returns to these supply and demand

98
00:07:02,130 --> 00:07:03,569
zones.

99
00:07:03,569 --> 00:07:08,620
But to effectively trade these zones, it is
important to understand the two key rules

100
00:07:08,620 --> 00:07:12,240
to identify the right zones on the chart.

101
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:17,759
The first rule is to trade only fresh and
untouched zones because supply and demand

102
00:07:17,759 --> 00:07:20,770
zones are one-time use.

103
00:07:20,770 --> 00:07:26,979
Once price hits a zone and reverses, the zone
loses its power, and the probability of it

104
00:07:26,979 --> 00:07:31,479
causing another reversal in the future is
lower.

105
00:07:31,479 --> 00:07:37,290
The second rule is that recent zones are more
important than older ones.

106
00:07:37,290 --> 00:07:42,960
Supply and demand areas that have been created
recently are far more effective than those

107
00:07:42,960 --> 00:07:45,530
that were created a long time ago.

108
00:07:45,530 --> 00:07:52,349
There are four distinct types of supply and
demand zones based on how the price approached

109
00:07:52,349 --> 00:07:53,599
and left the zone.

110
00:07:53,599 --> 00:08:00,000
These four types can be categorized into two
groups: continuation structures and reversal

111
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,910
structures.

112
00:08:01,910 --> 00:08:07,501
First continuation pattern is the Rally-base-Rally,
which forms a demand zone during an uptrend.

113
00:08:07,501 --> 00:08:15,539
The market structure begins with a rally,
followed by consolidation, and ends with another

114
00:08:15,539 --> 00:08:18,229
rally, which creates the demand zone.

115
00:08:18,229 --> 00:08:25,590
The second continuation pattern is the Drop-base-Drop
structure, which forms a supply zone during

116
00:08:25,590 --> 00:08:27,010
a downtrend.

117
00:08:27,010 --> 00:08:33,450
The market structure begins with a price decrease,
followed by consolidation, and ends with another

118
00:08:33,450 --> 00:08:37,520
price decrease, which creates a supply zone.

119
00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:43,539
In both cases, if the market returns to these
zones, the price is expected to move in the

120
00:08:43,539 --> 00:08:46,529
direction that created the zone.

121
00:08:46,529 --> 00:08:53,410
The Drop-base-Rally is the first reversal
structure, which forms a demand zone in the

122
00:08:53,410 --> 00:08:54,769
market.

123
00:08:54,769 --> 00:09:00,839
This zone is located where the market changes
from moving down to moving up.

124
00:09:00,839 --> 00:09:05,620
The second reversal structure is the Rally-base-Drop
pattern.

125
00:09:05,620 --> 00:09:11,410
This forms a supply zone when the market reverses
from moving higher to moving lower.

126
00:09:11,410 --> 00:09:17,579
Again, if the market returns to these zones,
the price is expected to move in the direction

127
00:09:17,579 --> 00:09:19,810
that created the zone.

128
00:09:19,810 --> 00:09:24,880
The main advantage of supply and demand trading
is that it helps you to understand the market

129
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:28,490
structure and market dynamics much better.

130
00:09:28,490 --> 00:09:34,600
This is the first component in your smart
money plan.

131
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:37,279
3.

132
00:09:37,279 --> 00:09:39,120
The Law of Effort and Result

133
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:43,200
The Law of Effort vs. Result is another fundamental
principle of Wyckoff Theory and one of the

134
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:47,810
most important concept to follow the smart
money on any market.

135
00:09:47,810 --> 00:09:53,720
This concept states that the effort made by
aggressive and passive buyers and sellers

136
00:09:53,720 --> 00:09:57,500
will be reflected in the price movement of
any market.

137
00:09:57,500 --> 00:10:02,930
The principle is based on the idea that the
market is a battle between buyers and sellers,

138
00:10:02,930 --> 00:10:08,589
and the direction of the market is determined
by the side with the greatest effort, which

139
00:10:08,589 --> 00:10:11,020
is represented by volume.

140
00:10:11,020 --> 00:10:17,990
High volume indicates strong market participation,
while low volume indicates weak market participation.

141
00:10:17,990 --> 00:10:25,279
Volume is very important because it provides
insight into market sentiment and future price

142
00:10:25,279 --> 00:10:26,279
movements.

143
00:10:26,279 --> 00:10:30,840
And it’s not difficult to understand once
you learn the basic principles of supply and

144
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,079
demand.

145
00:10:32,079 --> 00:10:36,720
This simply requires you to relate the volume
with price action.

146
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:37,720
4.

147
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:43,620
Volume Spread Analysis trading
If you want to identify the signs of market

148
00:10:43,620 --> 00:10:48,269
manipulation and follow the smart money's
footsteps, you need to learn Volume Spread

149
00:10:48,269 --> 00:10:49,870
Analysis.

150
00:10:49,870 --> 00:10:55,620
This is a game changer, and can give you an
edge over other traders who only look at price

151
00:10:55,620 --> 00:10:57,840
action or indicators.

152
00:10:57,840 --> 00:11:04,870
VSA can reveal when smart money is accumulating
or distributing an asset, when they are testing

153
00:11:04,870 --> 00:11:10,750
supply or demand, and when they are ready
to start a new trend or reverse an existing

154
00:11:10,750 --> 00:11:12,420
one.

155
00:11:12,420 --> 00:11:17,440
Volume Spread Analysis (VSA) is based on the
premise that volume is the fuel that drives

156
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:18,720
price movements.

157
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:25,769
Volume is the amount of trading activity in
a given period, while spread (or range) represents

158
00:11:25,769 --> 00:11:30,680
the difference between the open and close
prices of a candlestick.

159
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:36,730
By analyzing the relationship between volume
and spread, VSA can reveal the supply and

160
00:11:36,730 --> 00:11:39,519
demand dynamics in the market.

161
00:11:39,519 --> 00:11:46,790
It’s a lot to talk about, but the key concept
of VSA is that when volume and spread are

162
00:11:46,790 --> 00:11:52,570
in harmony, it means that there is a balance
between buyers and sellers, and the market

163
00:11:52,570 --> 00:11:55,899
is likely to continue in its current direction.

164
00:11:55,899 --> 00:12:02,250
However, when volume and spread are in disharmony,
it means that there is an imbalance between

165
00:12:02,250 --> 00:12:07,270
buyers and sellers, and the market is likely
to reverse or consolidate.

166
00:12:07,270 --> 00:12:13,500
So, when price and volume are moving in the
same direction, it is a sign that the price

167
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:16,220
move is strong and is likely to continue.

168
00:12:16,220 --> 00:12:22,589
For example, if a market is in an uptrend
and there is a significant increase in volume,

169
00:12:22,589 --> 00:12:26,240
it is a sign that the uptrend is likely to
continue.

170
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:31,920
Divergences between price and volume occur
when there is a disagreement between the price

171
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:34,980
action and the volume of that market.

172
00:12:34,980 --> 00:12:39,920
This can indicate that the price move is not
supported by market participation and may

173
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:41,389
not be sustainable.

174
00:12:41,389 --> 00:12:47,709
For example, if a market is in an uptrend,
but the volume is decreasing, it is a sign

175
00:12:47,709 --> 00:12:50,310
that the uptrend may not continue.

176
00:12:50,310 --> 00:12:55,480
So, VSA is the second component of our smart
money trading plan.

177
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:56,480
5.

178
00:12:56,480 --> 00:13:00,639
The Law of Cause and Effect

179
00:13:00,639 --> 00:13:05,839
Another important smart money concept states
that the differences between supply and demand

180
00:13:05,839 --> 00:13:07,279
are not random.

181
00:13:07,279 --> 00:13:13,079
Instead, they come after periods of preparation,
as a result of specific events.

182
00:13:13,079 --> 00:13:16,329
This is the law of cause and effect.

183
00:13:16,329 --> 00:13:22,960
For the market to develop an effect (trend),
first there must be a cause (namely, accumulation/distribution).

184
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:28,260
Basically, this law states that every price
move has a cause.

185
00:13:28,260 --> 00:13:33,260
Changes cannot happen out of nowhere and a
cause must be established first.

186
00:13:33,260 --> 00:13:38,620
This starts during periods of sideways movement
or when the market is ranging.

187
00:13:38,620 --> 00:13:44,540
This can be seen in charts when we have small
ranges or low volatility periods.

188
00:13:44,540 --> 00:13:50,139
The longer this process continues, the larger
the expected resulting move.

189
00:13:50,139 --> 00:13:57,079
So after a period of consolidation, there
is an expansion or explosive move in price.

190
00:13:57,079 --> 00:14:04,630
In Wyckoff's terms, a period of accumulation
(cause) eventually leads to an uptrend (effect).

191
00:14:04,630 --> 00:14:11,760
In contrast, a period of distribution (cause)
eventually results in a downtrend (effect).

192
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:12,760
6.

193
00:14:12,760 --> 00:14:20,399
The Composite Man
When I started to study Wyckoff, my first

194
00:14:20,399 --> 00:14:24,910
aha moment was when I was reading about the
Composite man.

195
00:14:24,910 --> 00:14:30,580
Wyckoff created the idea of the Composite
Man as an imaginary identity of the market.

196
00:14:30,580 --> 00:14:35,070
This single entity is responsible for controlling
the market.

197
00:14:35,070 --> 00:14:41,580
And it always acts in his own best interest
to ensure he can buy low and sell high.

198
00:14:41,580 --> 00:14:46,810
Think of composite man as an evil entity,
controlling markets by pushing buttons.

199
00:14:46,810 --> 00:14:53,000
His single objective is to move the markets
to your disadvantage, seeking to maximize

200
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:55,329
his profit at “your” expense.

201
00:14:55,329 --> 00:15:00,079
And he plans and executes his deceptions well
in advance.

202
00:15:00,079 --> 00:15:06,050
He’s basically there to fool you to buying
positions that he has already accumulated.

203
00:15:06,050 --> 00:15:09,790
He will tempt you to buy and sell at the worst
possible time.

204
00:15:09,790 --> 00:15:12,490
And it makes a lot of sense.

205
00:15:12,490 --> 00:15:16,070
Have you ever had the feeling that someone
is watching your positions?

206
00:15:16,070 --> 00:15:21,009
That you entered the market, and immediately
price went against you?

207
00:15:21,009 --> 00:15:26,519
Or the market is quiet, with low activity,
and as soon as you enter, the price starts

208
00:15:26,519 --> 00:15:27,949
jumping up and down?

209
00:15:27,949 --> 00:15:32,730
It’s like someone is driving prices, playing
with your emotions.

210
00:15:32,730 --> 00:15:39,180
In essence, the Composite Man represents the
biggest players (so-called smart money).

211
00:15:39,180 --> 00:15:46,899
It always acts in its interest to ensure that
it can buy at a discount and sell at a premium.

212
00:15:46,899 --> 00:15:52,980
The Composite Man’s behavior is the opposite
of retail traders, and in order to adapt to

213
00:15:52,980 --> 00:15:58,589
changing market conditions, we, retail traders,
must learn from his behavior.

214
00:15:58,589 --> 00:16:04,579
If you don’t understand the game as he plays
it, you’ll take the wrong side of the trade

215
00:16:04,579 --> 00:16:09,839
and you’ll sit in front if your screen,
desperate that the market moves once again,

216
00:16:09,839 --> 00:16:11,550
against your position.

217
00:16:11,550 --> 00:16:16,310
In order to understand the behavior of the
Composite man, you need to understand the

218
00:16:16,310 --> 00:16:17,529
concept of liquidity.

219
00:16:17,529 --> 00:16:18,529
7.

220
00:16:18,529 --> 00:16:23,209
Liquidity clear-outs

221
00:16:23,209 --> 00:16:27,890
In the world of smart money, it's important
to question the liquidity of the market you're

222
00:16:27,890 --> 00:16:29,230
trading.

223
00:16:29,230 --> 00:16:35,370
Whether you're trading the EUR/USD or Bitcoin
or Amazon, liquidity plays a crucial role

224
00:16:35,370 --> 00:16:37,670
in a market's functionality.

225
00:16:37,670 --> 00:16:43,709
In fact, an ample participation from buyers
and sellers is necessary for a market to be

226
00:16:43,709 --> 00:16:46,699
considered rich in liquidity.

227
00:16:46,699 --> 00:16:53,079
This is why market makers and smart money
often engage in liquidity hunting or liquidity

228
00:16:53,079 --> 00:16:59,680
clear-outs, which involves extracting liquidity
from the market by flushing out weak players.

229
00:16:59,680 --> 00:17:06,500
A Liquidity clear-out is when the price will
move just above or below an area where stop

230
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:13,089
loss orders of retail traders are placed,
executing those orders and reversing.

231
00:17:13,089 --> 00:17:18,679
The goal of this strategy is to take advantage
of the liquidity that is provided by the stop-loss

232
00:17:18,679 --> 00:17:22,079
orders of other traders.

233
00:17:22,079 --> 00:17:28,260
Liquidity hunting works by identifying areas
of high concentration of stop-loss orders

234
00:17:28,260 --> 00:17:29,760
in the market.

235
00:17:29,760 --> 00:17:36,450
These areas are usually near support and resistance
levels, where many traders place their stops

236
00:17:36,450 --> 00:17:39,190
to protect their positions.

237
00:17:39,190 --> 00:17:45,549
Smart money, or the Composite man, will then
push the price towards these levels, triggering

238
00:17:45,549 --> 00:17:51,120
the stop-loss orders and creating a spike
in volume and volatility.

239
00:17:51,120 --> 00:17:57,850
This spike can also cause other traders to
panic and join the move, creating a double

240
00:17:57,850 --> 00:17:58,850
trap.

241
00:17:58,850 --> 00:18:04,520
Once the liquidity hunters have filled their
orders at favorable prices, they will quickly

242
00:18:04,520 --> 00:18:09,860
reverse their positions and drive the price
back to its original range.

243
00:18:09,860 --> 00:18:15,760
This can leave many traders with losses or
missed opportunities, while the Composite

244
00:18:15,760 --> 00:18:18,650
Man profits from the price swing.

245
00:18:18,650 --> 00:18:24,410
This is one of the main strategies used by
smart money to make money.

246
00:18:24,410 --> 00:18:28,710
Liquidity is the third component in our smart
money trading plan.

247
00:18:28,710 --> 00:18:29,710
8.

248
00:18:29,710 --> 00:18:36,450
How to Think Like Smart Money
If you are a retail trader who wants to succeed

249
00:18:36,450 --> 00:18:41,520
in the market, you need to learn how to think
like a smart money trader.

250
00:18:41,520 --> 00:18:43,900
Imagine you don’t have a 5.000 dollars account.

251
00:18:43,900 --> 00:18:46,730
You have a 1 billion dollar account.

252
00:18:46,730 --> 00:18:52,120
You have the power to influence price movements
and develop trends on the market.

253
00:18:52,120 --> 00:18:58,470
You have access to more information, more
resources, and more capital than 99% of retail

254
00:18:58,470 --> 00:19:05,100
traders, and you need to use various tactics
to deceive and manipulate other traders to

255
00:19:05,100 --> 00:19:06,640
your advantage.

256
00:19:06,640 --> 00:19:07,919
How would you do it?

257
00:19:07,919 --> 00:19:10,039
You wouldn’t trade like most retail traders.

258
00:19:10,039 --> 00:19:16,380
You’re in the business of making money,
so you need many tactics to create false signals,

259
00:19:16,380 --> 00:19:19,090
traps, and illusions in the market.

260
00:19:19,090 --> 00:19:21,440
Here’s the reality.

261
00:19:21,440 --> 00:19:25,580
Smart money are not necessarily smarter than
retail traders.

262
00:19:25,580 --> 00:19:30,090
They are simply more experienced, disciplined,
and strategic.

263
00:19:30,090 --> 00:19:36,320
They have a clear understanding of how the
market works, how other traders behave, and

264
00:19:36,320 --> 00:19:39,500
how they can exploit their emotions and biases.

265
00:19:39,500 --> 00:19:44,309
They do not trade based on predictions, opinions,
or hopes.

266
00:19:44,309 --> 00:19:48,380
They trade based on probabilities, facts,
and evidence.

267
00:19:48,380 --> 00:19:52,160
Smart money does not care about being right
or wrong.

268
00:19:52,160 --> 00:19:54,380
They care about making money.

269
00:19:54,380 --> 00:19:57,930
They are flexible and adaptable to changing
market conditions.

270
00:19:57,930 --> 00:20:02,400
They do not chase after trades or revenge
trade.

271
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:08,480
They wait patiently for high-probability opportunities
and execute them with precision.

272
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:10,500
Smart money does not follow the crowd.

273
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:12,880
They lead the crowd.

274
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:17,530
They do not rely on lagging indicators, news,
or tips from others.

275
00:20:17,530 --> 00:20:20,410
They do not trade what they see or hear.

276
00:20:20,410 --> 00:20:23,130
They trade what they know and understand.

277
00:20:23,130 --> 00:20:25,080
They do not react to the market.

278
00:20:25,080 --> 00:20:26,080
They anticipate the market.

279
00:20:26,080 --> 00:20:27,080
9.

280
00:20:27,080 --> 00:20:34,190
The Tactics Used By Smart Money
Smart money knows that the market is a game

281
00:20:34,190 --> 00:20:36,559
of psychology and deception.

282
00:20:36,559 --> 00:20:43,020
They know that most retail traders are driven
by fear and greed, and they use these emotions

283
00:20:43,020 --> 00:20:44,429
against them.

284
00:20:44,429 --> 00:20:51,440
They use various tactics to create false signals,
traps, and illusions in the market that lure

285
00:20:51,440 --> 00:20:56,970
retail traders into making bad trades or missing
out on good ones.

286
00:20:56,970 --> 00:21:01,880
You already know their tactics very well,
you were the victim of those tactics on many

287
00:21:01,880 --> 00:21:06,470
occasions:
- Stop hunting is the most obvious strategy:

288
00:21:06,470 --> 00:21:12,029
This is when smart money pushes the price
to a level where they know many retail traders

289
00:21:12,029 --> 00:21:15,789
have placed their stop losses or take profits.

290
00:21:15,789 --> 00:21:22,240
This triggers a cascade of orders that either
liquidates their positions or fills their

291
00:21:22,240 --> 00:21:24,540
orders at unfavorable prices.

292
00:21:24,540 --> 00:21:31,890
This allows smart money to either exit their
positions with a profit or enter new positions

293
00:21:31,890 --> 00:21:34,419
with a better price.

294
00:21:34,419 --> 00:21:39,620
- Fakeouts are another tactic: This is when
smart money creates a false breakout of a

295
00:21:39,620 --> 00:21:45,850
support or resistance level that attracts
many retail traders to enter in the direction

296
00:21:45,850 --> 00:21:47,159
of the breakout.

297
00:21:47,159 --> 00:21:53,700
However, after a few candles, the price reverses
sharply in the opposite direction, trapping

298
00:21:53,700 --> 00:21:56,649
those traders in losing trades.

299
00:21:56,649 --> 00:22:02,950
- Whipsaws are another smart money tactic:
This is when smart money creates a lot of

300
00:22:02,950 --> 00:22:10,029
volatility and noise in the market that confuses
many retail traders and makes them second-guess

301
00:22:10,029 --> 00:22:11,400
their trades.

302
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:17,270
The price moves up and down rapidly without
any clear direction or trend, causing many

303
00:22:17,270 --> 00:22:24,049
traders to exit their trades prematurely or
switch sides frequently.

304
00:22:24,049 --> 00:22:30,380
The reality is that many retail traders will
use the same price levels to place their entries

305
00:22:30,380 --> 00:22:31,590
or stop losses.

306
00:22:31,590 --> 00:22:37,669
And these are the perfect zones for smart
money to trigger one of their traps.

307
00:22:37,669 --> 00:22:43,470
You might ask: why is this difference between
us, retail traders, and smart money?

308
00:22:43,470 --> 00:22:50,720
Because they don’t trade like us, using
technical analysis, indicators or chart patterns.

309
00:22:50,720 --> 00:22:55,929
Institutional players cannot trade the same
as the retail trader, because in low liquidity

310
00:22:55,929 --> 00:23:00,929
price areas, they will push price far away
with large orders.

311
00:23:00,929 --> 00:23:07,830
So they must use high liquidity zones to put
their own large orders in the market without

312
00:23:07,830 --> 00:23:09,600
having too much impact on the price.

313
00:23:09,600 --> 00:23:10,600
10.

314
00:23:10,600 --> 00:23:13,400
Smart money traps - Fake breakout at the high/low
of the day

315
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:20,130
Now let’s go even deeper and let’s discuss
about the most common smart money traps.

316
00:23:20,130 --> 00:23:24,940
If you are a day trader, you have probably
experienced the frustration of being stopped

317
00:23:24,940 --> 00:23:31,210
out of a trade by a sudden spike in price
at the high or low of the day.

318
00:23:31,210 --> 00:23:36,289
This practice is one of the most common ways
that smart money manipulates the market to

319
00:23:36,289 --> 00:23:38,520
trap retail traders.

320
00:23:38,520 --> 00:23:44,320
These are price movement that break a significant
level of support or resistance, in this case

321
00:23:44,320 --> 00:23:51,150
the high or low of the day, but fail to sustain
the momentum and quickly reverse back into

322
00:23:51,150 --> 00:23:53,159
the previous range.

323
00:23:53,159 --> 00:23:55,220
Fake breakouts come with a higher volatility.

324
00:23:55,220 --> 00:23:58,150
You see them often, on any market.

325
00:23:58,150 --> 00:24:03,840
Here’s a fake breakout at the high of the
day, when price breaks above the highest point

326
00:24:03,840 --> 00:24:08,429
reached during the trading session, but then
falls back below it.

327
00:24:08,429 --> 00:24:14,640
And here’s a fake breakout at the low of
the day, when price breaks below the lowest

328
00:24:14,640 --> 00:24:20,580
point reached during the trading session,
but then rises back above it.

329
00:24:20,580 --> 00:24:26,539
Smart money uses these fake breakouts for
two main reasons: to shake out weak hands

330
00:24:26,539 --> 00:24:29,330
and to accumulate or distribute positions.

331
00:24:29,330 --> 00:24:36,120
Shaking out weak hands means forcing retail
traders to exit their trades prematurely by

332
00:24:36,120 --> 00:24:39,140
creating fear or greed.

333
00:24:39,140 --> 00:24:45,270
Smart money may push the price above the high
of the day to trigger stop losses and buy

334
00:24:45,270 --> 00:24:49,809
orders from retail traders who are following
the breakout.

335
00:24:49,809 --> 00:24:53,710
This creates a surge in demand that drives
the price higher.

336
00:24:53,710 --> 00:25:00,230
However, once smart money has filled their
orders, they will dump their positions, causing

337
00:25:00,230 --> 00:25:06,309
the price to fall back below the high of the
day and trapping retail traders who bought

338
00:25:06,309 --> 00:25:07,539
at the top.

339
00:25:07,539 --> 00:25:13,870
This also creates a supply and volume imbalance
that drives the price lower.

340
00:25:13,870 --> 00:25:19,550
You can identify this type of fake breakouts
by carefully analyzing the volume and some

341
00:25:19,550 --> 00:25:22,380
common price action patterns.

342
00:25:22,380 --> 00:25:28,400
Fake breakouts often form specific price action
patterns that signal a reversal or continuation

343
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:29,400
of the trend.

344
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:36,669
For example, a double top at the high of the
day, after a fake breakout, or double bottom

345
00:25:36,669 --> 00:25:43,330
pattern at the low of the day, again, after
a fake breakout, is a clear sign of market

346
00:25:43,330 --> 00:25:44,870
manipulation.

347
00:25:44,870 --> 00:25:48,980
If you find a reversal candlestick pattern,
that even better.

348
00:25:48,980 --> 00:25:54,540
Fake breakouts often form specific candlestick
patterns that indicate bullish or bearish

349
00:25:54,540 --> 00:25:56,549
sentiment in the market.

350
00:25:56,549 --> 00:26:03,950
For example, a pin bar or a candle with large
wick is a clear sign of rejection after a

351
00:26:03,950 --> 00:26:05,649
failed breakout.

352
00:26:05,649 --> 00:26:12,480
Asian session trap
The Asian trading session is one of the main

353
00:26:12,480 --> 00:26:15,059
zones targeted by the smart money.

354
00:26:15,059 --> 00:26:21,960
The Tokyo range trap is a common phenomenon
if you’re trading Forex, crypto and indices,

355
00:26:21,960 --> 00:26:27,789
and occurs during the Asian session, which
is typically characterized by low volatility

356
00:26:27,789 --> 00:26:29,860
and tight trading ranges.

357
00:26:29,860 --> 00:26:36,020
The Tokyo range trap refers to the situation
where smart money use the range of the session

358
00:26:36,020 --> 00:26:42,840
to trap retail traders into false breakouts
and reversals, and then exploit their positions

359
00:26:42,840 --> 00:26:48,799
during the London and New York sessions, which
are more volatile and liquid.

360
00:26:48,799 --> 00:26:54,520
One of the most common tactics is to create
a false breakout of the Tokyo range, which

361
00:26:54,520 --> 00:26:59,330
is the high and low of the price action during
the Tokyo session.

362
00:26:59,330 --> 00:27:05,130
Price moves beyond the range, and then quickly
reverses and moves back into the range.

363
00:27:05,130 --> 00:27:11,210
This creates a false signal for the average
retail trader, who may enter or exit trades

364
00:27:11,210 --> 00:27:16,970
based on the breakout, only to find himself
trapped in losing positions when the price

365
00:27:16,970 --> 00:27:19,100
moves against him.

366
00:27:19,100 --> 00:27:24,840
Another tactic used by smart money traders
is to create a false reversal of the Tokyo

367
00:27:24,840 --> 00:27:28,440
range, which is the opposite of a false breakout.

368
00:27:28,440 --> 00:27:34,370
How to avoid falling into the Tokyo range
trap and even make some money?

369
00:27:34,370 --> 00:27:40,500
One of the most effective ways is to use volume
to measure the strength of the breakout.

370
00:27:40,500 --> 00:27:46,960
A high volume outside the Tokio range indicates
that there is strong market participation

371
00:27:46,960 --> 00:27:53,929
and conviction behind a price movement, while
a low volume indicates that there is weak

372
00:27:53,929 --> 00:27:58,899
market participation and low conviction behind
a price movement.

373
00:27:58,899 --> 00:28:07,039
Therefore, a high volume breakout or reversal
is more likely to be genuine than a low volume

374
00:28:07,039 --> 00:28:08,380
one.

375
00:28:08,380 --> 00:28:15,470
Additionally, you can learn from past examples
of how the Tokyo range trap has affected market

376
00:28:15,470 --> 00:28:16,700
trends.

377
00:28:16,700 --> 00:28:22,279
If you analyze these consecutive Tokyo sessions
we see an interesting pattern:

378
00:28:22,279 --> 00:28:28,950
Range traders who have taken short positions
at the top of the Asian range had their stop

379
00:28:28,950 --> 00:28:31,450
losses hunted, outside of the range.

380
00:28:31,450 --> 00:28:36,980
Each time, the market reversed aggressively
in the opposite direction.

381
00:28:36,980 --> 00:28:43,659
The upward movement outside of the range also
seduced traders to take long positions, hoping

382
00:28:43,659 --> 00:28:45,070
for a breakout trade.

383
00:28:45,070 --> 00:28:48,909
That’s the second batch of traders, who
were trapped.

384
00:28:48,909 --> 00:28:55,570
Long breakout traders.

385
00:28:55,570 --> 00:28:56,570
Wedges triangles trap

386
00:28:56,570 --> 00:29:01,179
Wedges and triangles are two of the most common
chart patterns that traders use to identify

387
00:29:01,179 --> 00:29:04,910
potential reversals or continuations in the
market.

388
00:29:04,910 --> 00:29:09,130
However, not all wedges and triangles are
genuine.

389
00:29:09,130 --> 00:29:16,419
Sometimes, they are deliberately created by
smart money, to trap retailer traders.

390
00:29:16,419 --> 00:29:21,350
Wedges and triangles are usually formed by
two converging trend lines that connect the

391
00:29:21,350 --> 00:29:24,299
highs and lows of a price action.

392
00:29:24,299 --> 00:29:29,710
They indicate a period of consolidation, where
the market is indecisive and the trading range

393
00:29:29,710 --> 00:29:30,840
narrows.

394
00:29:30,840 --> 00:29:37,950
Now, smart money knows that many traders rely
on wedges and triangles to make their trading

395
00:29:37,950 --> 00:29:38,950
decisions.

396
00:29:38,950 --> 00:29:44,830
Therefore, they can use these patterns to
create false signals and lure unsuspecting

397
00:29:44,830 --> 00:29:47,090
traders into their traps.

398
00:29:47,090 --> 00:29:53,560
You’ll often see that price breaks out of
a wedge or a triangle in one direction, but

399
00:29:53,560 --> 00:29:57,330
then quickly reverses and moves in the opposite
direction.

400
00:29:57,330 --> 00:30:03,450
This creates confusion and panic among traders
who followed the initial breakout signal and

401
00:30:03,450 --> 00:30:05,880
entered positions in that direction.

402
00:30:05,880 --> 00:30:10,580
The idea is to trap traders on the wrong side
of the market.

403
00:30:10,580 --> 00:30:17,540
For example, smart money can create an ascending
triangle pattern in an uptrend and induce

404
00:30:17,540 --> 00:30:20,149
a fake breakout to the upside.

405
00:30:20,149 --> 00:30:24,510
This will attract buyers who think that the
uptrend will continue.

406
00:30:24,510 --> 00:30:30,850
However, smart money will then sell their
positions at higher prices and drive the price

407
00:30:30,850 --> 00:30:38,320
down below the lower trend line of the triangle,
triggering stop losses and creating more selling

408
00:30:38,320 --> 00:30:39,370
pressure.

409
00:30:39,370 --> 00:30:46,950
This will result in a sharp decline in price
and a minor reversal of the uptrend.

410
00:30:46,950 --> 00:30:49,169
Stop loss hunting is also common.

411
00:30:49,169 --> 00:30:55,020
This occurs when smart money pushes the price
to a level where many traders have placed

412
00:30:55,020 --> 00:31:01,929
their stop losses, triggering them and causing
a sudden spike or drop in price.

413
00:31:01,929 --> 00:31:08,309
Smart money can use stop runs to shake out
weak traders from their positions and create

414
00:31:08,309 --> 00:31:10,880
liquidity for their own trades.

415
00:31:10,880 --> 00:31:17,309
For example, they can create a symmetrical
triangle pattern in a sideways market and

416
00:31:17,309 --> 00:31:21,700
induce stop runs on both sides of the triangle.

417
00:31:21,700 --> 00:31:27,280
This will cause traders who entered positions
based on either side of the breakout to exit

418
00:31:27,280 --> 00:31:29,620
their trades at a loss.

419
00:31:29,620 --> 00:31:35,640
Smart money will then take advantage of this
liquidity and enter positions in their desired

420
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:36,640
direction.

421
00:31:36,640 --> 00:31:44,269
From my experience, it’s very hard to know
for sure whether a wedge or a triangle pattern

422
00:31:44,269 --> 00:31:46,519
is genuine or fake.

423
00:31:46,519 --> 00:31:53,260
In this example, you can observe that on the
lower boundary of the wedge, the lows become

424
00:31:53,260 --> 00:31:57,830
slightly higher each time it comes down to
the line.

425
00:31:57,830 --> 00:32:02,850
This has the effect of ensuring that none
of the trades that have taken short positions

426
00:32:02,850 --> 00:32:05,870
in these regions can turn a profit.

427
00:32:05,870 --> 00:32:11,679
Similarly, on the upper boundary of the wedge,
the same thing is happening with each of the

428
00:32:11,679 --> 00:32:18,779
highs becoming progressively lower and trapping
the long traders and pulling them down.

429
00:32:18,779 --> 00:32:23,809
There is no way of predicting which direction
the price will ultimately breakout.

430
00:32:23,809 --> 00:32:27,700
I personally avoid trading during this type
of consolidation.

431
00:32:27,700 --> 00:32:33,730
But if you want to be active in the market,
volume is the only indicator that will help

432
00:32:33,730 --> 00:32:36,789
you to anticipate the future direction.

433
00:32:36,789 --> 00:32:43,470
Generally, volume should decrease as a wedge
or a triangle pattern forms, indicating that

434
00:32:43,470 --> 00:32:51,470
traders are waiting for a breakout signal.

435
00:32:51,470 --> 00:32:54,350
Market open manipulation
Market open manipulation is another common

436
00:32:54,350 --> 00:33:00,389
trap, which refers to the deliberate actions
of smart money to create false impressions

437
00:33:00,389 --> 00:33:03,419
of supply and demand in the market.

438
00:33:03,419 --> 00:33:08,380
These actions are designed to influence the
price movements and the psychology of retail

439
00:33:08,380 --> 00:33:14,010
traders, who often trade based on technical
analysis, indicators or news.

440
00:33:14,010 --> 00:33:18,330
It’s a reality that every trader has to
face and deal with.

441
00:33:18,330 --> 00:33:24,799
The market open manipulation happens for two
main reasons: smart money want to take profit

442
00:33:24,799 --> 00:33:31,090
from their existing positions or to accumulate
or distribute more positions at favorable

443
00:33:31,090 --> 00:33:32,090
prices.

444
00:33:32,090 --> 00:33:38,630
For example, if smart money wants to sell
a large position, they may drive up the price

445
00:33:38,630 --> 00:33:39,889
at the market open.

446
00:33:39,889 --> 00:33:45,860
This will attract retail traders who buy into
the breakout, thinking that the market is

447
00:33:45,860 --> 00:33:47,500
going to rally.

448
00:33:47,500 --> 00:33:54,070
However, once enough retail traders are trapped
in their long positions, smart money will

449
00:33:54,070 --> 00:33:59,430
dump their positions into the market, causing
the price to reverse.

450
00:33:59,430 --> 00:34:04,880
This will trigger stop-loss orders and panic
selling from retail traders.

451
00:34:04,880 --> 00:34:12,909
There are many types of market open manipulation
that smart money can use to trick retail traders.

452
00:34:12,909 --> 00:34:17,919
By now, you already know them:
- Fake breakouts: This is when smart money

453
00:34:17,919 --> 00:34:24,359
pushes the price above or below a significant
support or resistance level, only to reverse

454
00:34:24,359 --> 00:34:26,339
it shortly after.

455
00:34:26,339 --> 00:34:31,790
This creates a false signal that the market
is trending in one direction, when in fact

456
00:34:31,790 --> 00:34:34,089
it is going in the opposite direction.

457
00:34:34,089 --> 00:34:40,790
- Stop-loss hunting: This is when smart money
targets the areas where retail traders place

458
00:34:40,790 --> 00:34:47,740
their stop-loss orders, such as below support
levels or above resistance levels.

459
00:34:47,740 --> 00:34:54,389
- False signals: This is when smart money
uses indicators, news events, or other factors

460
00:34:54,389 --> 00:34:59,880
to generate misleading signals that contradict
the actual market direction.

461
00:34:59,880 --> 00:35:07,410
For example, smart money may release positive
news about a stock before the market open,

462
00:35:07,410 --> 00:35:11,460
causing retail traders to buy into the hype.

463
00:35:11,460 --> 00:35:15,920
Or they deliberately move the price above
a common moving average, to determine moving

464
00:35:15,920 --> 00:35:17,760
average traders to enter.

465
00:35:17,760 --> 00:35:24,640
And, once the market opens, smart money will
sell their positions at a high price and then

466
00:35:24,640 --> 00:35:28,010
drive the price down.

467
00:35:28,010 --> 00:35:32,480
During the market open manipulation, you’ll
witness increased volatility.

468
00:35:32,480 --> 00:35:38,640
You’ll see fast price swings and fluctuations
in a short period of time.

469
00:35:38,640 --> 00:35:43,450
This increases the risk for retail traders
who may get caught on the wrong side of the

470
00:35:43,450 --> 00:35:45,140
market.

471
00:35:45,140 --> 00:35:51,380
Market open manipulation can reduce the liquidity
in the market by creating artificial supply

472
00:35:51,380 --> 00:35:53,810
and demand imbalances.

473
00:35:53,810 --> 00:36:00,190
This can make it harder for retail traders
to enter or exit their positions at favorable

474
00:36:00,190 --> 00:36:01,470
prices.

475
00:36:01,470 --> 00:36:06,810
For a beginner trader, it’s very hard to
make money in these conditions.

476
00:36:06,810 --> 00:36:13,319
Market open trap can distort the true direction
and strength of the market trends by creating

477
00:36:13,319 --> 00:36:16,450
false breakouts or reversals.

478
00:36:16,450 --> 00:36:22,910
This will confuse retail traders who rely
on trend-following strategies or indicators.

479
00:36:22,910 --> 00:36:26,940
Accumulation / distribution trap

480
00:36:26,940 --> 00:36:32,660
I hope you realize that trading is a game
of psychology and strategy, where smart money

481
00:36:32,660 --> 00:36:39,030
traders try to outsmart and outplay retail
traders who often lack the knowledge, experience

482
00:36:39,030 --> 00:36:41,230
and discipline to succeed in the market.

483
00:36:41,230 --> 00:36:48,170
One of the ways that smart money gain an edge
over retail traders is by using accumulation

484
00:36:48,170 --> 00:36:53,130
and distribution strategies to manipulate
and trap them.

485
00:36:53,130 --> 00:36:58,420
Accumulation is the phase where smart money
traders buy or accumulate an asset at low

486
00:36:58,420 --> 00:37:02,619
prices, creating a strong demand.

487
00:37:02,619 --> 00:37:07,060
Distribution is the phase where smart money
traders sell or distribute their positions

488
00:37:07,060 --> 00:37:11,520
at high prices, creating a strong supply.

489
00:37:11,520 --> 00:37:16,620
The goal of these accumulation and distribution
strategies is to create false signals and

490
00:37:16,620 --> 00:37:23,630
expectations in the market that lure retail
traders into buying or selling at the wrong

491
00:37:23,630 --> 00:37:25,770
time.

492
00:37:25,770 --> 00:37:31,230
For example, during an accumulation phase,
smart money traders may create a downtrend

493
00:37:31,230 --> 00:37:37,900
or a consolidation pattern, making it appear
that the market is weak or bearish.

494
00:37:37,900 --> 00:37:44,410
This may induce retail traders to sell their
positions or short the market, expecting further

495
00:37:44,410 --> 00:37:45,910
price declines.

496
00:37:45,910 --> 00:37:53,400
However, once smart money traders have accumulated
enough positions at low prices, they may suddenly

497
00:37:53,400 --> 00:38:01,500
reverse the trend and push the price up, triggering
stop losses of retail traders with short positions.

498
00:38:01,500 --> 00:38:07,890
This creates a bullish breakout that attracts
more buyers into the market, allowing smart

499
00:38:07,890 --> 00:38:13,670
money traders to distribute their positions
at high prices.

500
00:38:13,670 --> 00:38:19,770
During a distribution phase, smart money may
create an uptrend or a consolidation pattern,

501
00:38:19,770 --> 00:38:23,160
making it to appear that the market is strong
and bullish.

502
00:38:23,160 --> 00:38:28,610
This may induce retail traders to go long,
expecting further price increases.

503
00:38:28,610 --> 00:38:34,990
And, once smart money have distributed enough
positions at high prices, they may suddenly

504
00:38:34,990 --> 00:38:41,260
reverse the trend and push the price down,
triggering stop losses of retail traders who

505
00:38:41,260 --> 00:38:42,400
went long.

506
00:38:42,400 --> 00:38:49,230
This creates a bearish breakdown that attracts
more sellers into the market, allowing smart

507
00:38:49,230 --> 00:38:55,640
money traders to accumulate more positions
at low prices.

508
00:38:55,640 --> 00:39:01,890
Smart money traders often use volume to confirm
or conceal their accumulation and distribution

509
00:39:01,890 --> 00:39:02,890
strategies.

510
00:39:02,890 --> 00:39:09,770
For example, during an accumulation phase,
smart money traders may use low volume to

511
00:39:09,770 --> 00:39:15,170
hide their buying activity and create a false
sense of weakness in the market.

512
00:39:15,170 --> 00:39:21,280
But, if you analyze price action during this
phase, you’ll see higher lows at the bottom

513
00:39:21,280 --> 00:39:25,300
of the accumulation, a bullish signal.

514
00:39:25,300 --> 00:39:31,480
Then smart money traders will use support
and resistance to test and break the confidence

515
00:39:31,480 --> 00:39:37,819
and conviction of retail traders by creating
false breakouts that trap them on the wrong

516
00:39:37,819 --> 00:39:40,000
side of the market.

517
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:45,390
During an accumulation phase, smart money
traders will usually use the support level

518
00:39:45,390 --> 00:39:51,720
to create false breakdowns that make retail
traders think that the price will fall further

519
00:39:51,720 --> 00:39:53,109
below support.

520
00:39:53,109 --> 00:39:54,109
11.

521
00:39:54,109 --> 00:39:57,960
How To Align With Smart Money

522
00:39:57,960 --> 00:40:04,270
Trading will always be a game between the
smart money against the dumb money.

523
00:40:04,270 --> 00:40:09,490
Retail traders might see some patterns as
continuation ones, but the smart money are

524
00:40:09,490 --> 00:40:11,990
seeing them as reversal patterns.

525
00:40:11,990 --> 00:40:15,579
You’ve seen the different traps used by
big players.

526
00:40:15,579 --> 00:40:21,780
In order to align yourself with their true
intentions, always remember that smart money

527
00:40:21,780 --> 00:40:28,170
are always searching for pockets of liquidity
in order to fill their desired positions in

528
00:40:28,170 --> 00:40:29,310
the market.

529
00:40:29,310 --> 00:40:35,430
They are always looking to shake out weak
hands, particularly around support and resistance

530
00:40:35,430 --> 00:40:38,440
levels that are being widely watched.

531
00:40:38,440 --> 00:40:44,550
It’s time to reconsider how you trade and
to start building a strategy that allows you

532
00:40:44,550 --> 00:40:51,900
to join the smart money, after a liquidity
clear-out, or after an obvious market trap.

533
00:40:51,900 --> 00:40:58,980
Again, the big players need LOTS of liquidity
in order to fill their massive orders.

534
00:40:58,980 --> 00:41:00,910
How do they get this liquidity?

535
00:41:00,910 --> 00:41:08,430
By creating well known retail chart patterns
and traps in order to involve the retail traders

536
00:41:08,430 --> 00:41:09,640
into the market.

537
00:41:09,640 --> 00:41:16,290
So, remember this, never enter a position
if you haven’t spotted a recent liquidity

538
00:41:16,290 --> 00:41:17,290
clear-out.

539
00:41:17,290 --> 00:41:22,550
For retail traders like you and me, the aim
should be to spot such potential liquidity

540
00:41:22,550 --> 00:41:29,180
zones and join the game of market maker and
to avoid being a liquidity target.

541
00:41:29,180 --> 00:41:35,859
The simplest structure to pay attention to
are zones with equal highs or lows.

542
00:41:35,859 --> 00:41:41,980
Always assume smart money will want to trap
traders around these areas.

543
00:41:41,980 --> 00:41:49,240
A liquidity clear out should always present
itself with a rapid, strong reversal move

544
00:41:49,240 --> 00:41:56,859
after a critical area is taken out—basically
a rapid rotation of price back into the previous

545
00:41:56,859 --> 00:41:58,230
trading range.

546
00:41:58,230 --> 00:42:03,660
And always monitor the lowest low or highest
high of a structure.

547
00:42:03,660 --> 00:42:10,310
If the structure is not even on highs or lows
positioning (for example, when highs or lows

548
00:42:10,310 --> 00:42:16,470
are connected through a trend line instead
of flat line), then the main area to watch

549
00:42:16,470 --> 00:42:23,339
is the lowest low or highest high of structure,
because this is where the majority of stop

550
00:42:23,339 --> 00:42:29,000
losses will sit and where breakout traders
might initiate other positions.

551
00:42:29,000 --> 00:42:30,000
12.

552
00:42:30,000 --> 00:42:33,970
Strategy no.1: Demand zone entry after liquidity
clear-out

553
00:42:33,970 --> 00:42:39,940
My favorite way to align my positions with
the ones of smart money is to trade demand

554
