650
00:55:29,580 --> 00:56:45,470
Strategy no.5 – Over and under break of
structure

651
00:56:45,470 --> 00:56:49,990
The over and under break of structure is another
way to align yourself with the big players.

652
00:56:49,990 --> 00:56:55,569
The break of structure is the first sign that
smart money have initiated a price shift.

653
00:56:55,569 --> 00:57:01,119
For a bearish over and under pattern, after
a previous uptrend.

654
00:57:01,119 --> 00:57:04,680
• Price creates a higher high
• then creates a lower high

655
00:57:04,680 --> 00:57:09,640
• Price breaks the previous high and creates
a new higher high

656
00:57:09,640 --> 00:57:16,700
• Then price breaks the previous low as
well and forms a lower low

657
00:57:16,700 --> 00:57:21,890
For a bullish over and under pattern, after
a previous downtrend.

658
00:57:21,890 --> 00:57:25,709
• Price creates a lower low
• Price creates a lower high

659
00:57:25,709 --> 00:57:30,699
• Price breaks the previous low and creates
a new lower low

660
00:57:30,699 --> 00:57:36,450
• Then price breaks the previous high as
well and forms a higher high

661
00:57:36,450 --> 00:57:42,809
Now, this break of structure doesn’t always
result in a reversal.

662
00:57:42,809 --> 00:57:49,520
That’s why, in order to align your positions
with the smart money, you need to use once

663
00:57:49,520 --> 00:57:53,049
again, supply and demand zones.

664
00:57:53,049 --> 00:57:58,780
So the plan is to find the break of structure
pattern, to wait for a retracement, and to

665
00:57:58,780 --> 00:58:05,319
find a supply or demand zone for an entry,
to execute the trade with a higher accuracy.

666
00:58:05,319 --> 00:58:10,230
Here, we see a significant decrease in price
on EUR/USD.

667
00:58:10,230 --> 00:58:14,380
The price makes a swing low, followed by a
lower high.

668
00:58:14,380 --> 00:58:20,760
Then makes a lower low, and it shoots up and
breaks the previous high, making a higher

669
00:58:20,760 --> 00:58:22,160
high.

670
00:58:22,160 --> 00:58:24,160
We have our break of structure and our over
and under pattern.

671
00:58:24,160 --> 00:58:27,480
Now we need to find a demand zone for an entry.

672
00:58:27,480 --> 00:58:33,500
First, you need to take a look at the left-hand
side of previous low, where the strong rally

673
00:58:33,500 --> 00:58:35,069
has started.

674
00:58:35,069 --> 00:58:39,020
You need to find the last bearish candle before
the strong rally.

675
00:58:39,020 --> 00:58:45,880
I see a rally base rally formation, which
is a continuation pattern, forming a demand

676
00:58:45,880 --> 00:58:47,369
zone.

677
00:58:47,369 --> 00:58:54,150
When price returns to this area, you can open
a buy position, with stops below this demand

678
00:58:54,150 --> 00:58:55,150
zone.

679
00:58:55,150 --> 00:58:59,530
If you find a liquidity clear-out, again,
even better.

680
00:58:59,530 --> 00:59:03,050
Here’s another break of structure pattern,
a bearish one.

681
00:59:03,050 --> 00:59:06,089
The previous trend is an uptrend.

682
00:59:06,089 --> 00:59:12,230
The price is forming a new swing high, declines,
then forms a swing low.

683
00:59:12,230 --> 00:59:18,450
Price then rallies again to exceed the previous
high (making a higher high).

684
00:59:18,450 --> 00:59:21,539
Then it decreased to form a new lower low.

685
00:59:21,539 --> 00:59:26,500
This is our first sign that we might have
an over and under pattern.

686
00:59:26,500 --> 00:59:31,869
Remember, you don’t enter just because you
find a possible break of structure.

687
00:59:31,869 --> 00:59:38,010
You need to wait for price to rise again,
to a fresh and untested supply area.

688
00:59:38,010 --> 00:59:44,000
You look at the left side of the previous
high where the previous strong down move started.

689
00:59:44,000 --> 00:59:51,240
I see a drop base drop formation, which is
a continuation pattern, forming a supply zone.

690
00:59:51,240 --> 00:59:58,000
When price returns to this area, you can open
a sell position, with stops above this supply

691
00:59:58,000 --> 01:00:29,470
zone.

692
01:00:29,470 --> 01:01:32,910
Strategy no.6 – Psychological numbers VSA
clear-out

693
01:01:32,910 --> 01:01:36,450
Psychological numbers are quite important
for smart money traders.

694
01:01:36,450 --> 01:01:42,230
These are price levels that have a significant
impact on the market sentiment and behavior.

695
01:01:42,230 --> 01:01:46,980
They are often round numbers or multiples
of 50, 100, etc.

696
01:01:46,980 --> 01:01:53,799
These numbers tend to act as support and resistance
levels, as well as trigger points for stop-losses

697
01:01:53,799 --> 01:01:55,940
and take-profits.

698
01:01:55,940 --> 01:02:01,020
These round numbers reflect the collective
psychology of the market participants, especially

699
01:02:01,020 --> 01:02:06,089
the large institutional traders who have the
power to move the market.

700
01:02:06,089 --> 01:02:12,740
One simple way to identify psychological numbers
is to look at the price charts and observe

701
01:02:12,740 --> 01:02:17,950
how the price reacts when it approaches or
breaks these levels.

702
01:02:17,950 --> 01:02:25,109
You will often see increased volatility, increased
volume, and many liquidity clear-outs around

703
01:02:25,109 --> 01:02:27,010
these levels.

704
01:02:27,010 --> 01:02:33,960
Supply and demand areas in combination with
round numbers is a powerful way to align yourself

705
01:02:33,960 --> 01:02:35,450
with the smart money.

706
01:02:35,450 --> 01:02:43,609
A supply zone, in combination with a psychological
level, is a good area to initiate a sell position.

707
01:02:43,609 --> 01:02:50,220
A demand zone, which includes psychological
level, again, offers a low risk - high reward

708
01:02:50,220 --> 01:02:52,530
buy situation.

709
01:02:52,530 --> 01:02:59,650
Liquidity clear-outs in combination with round
numbers is one of the simplest way to trade.

710
01:02:59,650 --> 01:03:05,070
If you know the main VSA patterns you’ll
have even better chances to trade with the

711
01:03:05,070 --> 01:03:06,320
smart money.

712
01:03:06,320 --> 01:03:10,829
Here’s Amazon, with the main psychological
levels added.

713
01:03:10,829 --> 01:03:15,940
Have a look at this liquidity run, just below
the price of 90$.

714
01:03:15,940 --> 01:03:18,790
And look at the candle which broke below the
level.

715
01:03:18,790 --> 01:03:22,119
It’s a down thrust VSA pattern.

716
01:03:22,119 --> 01:03:25,829
A bullish pin bar having an ultra-high volume.

717
01:03:25,829 --> 01:03:29,500
In fact it’s the highest volume in recent
period.

718
01:03:29,500 --> 01:03:33,859
The spread of the down thrust is low while
the volume is relatively high.

719
01:03:33,859 --> 01:03:40,670
So, there is more demand than supply, a sign
that price to rise in near future.

720
01:03:40,670 --> 01:03:45,730
And it happened at a very important psychological
number of 90$.

721
01:03:45,730 --> 01:03:47,540
And we had a liquidity clear-out.

722
01:03:47,540 --> 01:03:50,839
This buy right here is a no brainer.

723
01:03:50,839 --> 01:03:56,569
Here’s Apple, with the main psychological
levels added.

724
01:03:56,569 --> 01:04:04,440
I see an obvious liquidity run, taking stops
above 150$ and trapping long traders above

725
01:04:04,440 --> 01:04:05,790
this level.

726
01:04:05,790 --> 01:04:08,849
And look at the candle which broke below the
level.

727
01:04:08,849 --> 01:04:11,950
It’s an up thrust VSA pattern.

728
01:04:11,950 --> 01:04:14,430
A pin bar having above average volume.

729
01:04:14,430 --> 01:04:19,770
The spread of the up thrust is low while the
volume is relatively high.

730
01:04:19,770 --> 01:04:26,530
So, there is more supply than demand, a sign
that price could fall in near future.

731
01:04:26,530 --> 01:04:29,460
And it happened at a clear supply area.

732
01:04:29,460 --> 01:04:31,339
It’s right here.

733
01:04:31,339 --> 01:04:35,170
So we had the liquidity clear-out.

734
01:04:35,170 --> 01:04:36,900
The 150$ psychological number.

735
01:04:36,900 --> 01:04:38,420
A supply area.

736
01:04:38,420 --> 01:04:41,730
And the up thrust VSA pattern.

737
01:04:41,730 --> 01:04:42,849
Perfect sell trade.

738
01:04:42,849 --> 01:04:44,799
These trades are rare.

739
01:04:44,799 --> 01:04:51,549
You’ll be lucky if you find one trade per
week, with a supply or demand area, a VSA

740
01:04:51,549 --> 01:04:55,760
pattern, a liquidity run and psychological
number confluence.

741
